        <bioghist id="ref3">
            <head>History</head>
            <p>Men's basketball at the 
                <corpname>University of Connecticut</corpname> began with a single game played by what was then 
                <corpname>Connecticut Agricultural College</corpname> against 
                <corpname>Windham High School</corpname> in January 1901. The college team won, and by 1903, basketball was a varsity sport.</p>
            <p>
                <emph render="bold">Coaches:</emph></p>
            <list type="ordered">
                <item>No coach (1900–1915)</item>
                <item>John F. Donahue (1915–1919)</item>
                <item>M. R. Schwartz (1919–1921)</item>
                <item>J. Wilder Tasker (1921–1922)</item>
                <item>Roy Guyer (1922–1923)</item>
                <item>Sumner Dole (1923–1927)</item>
                <item>Louis Alexander (1927–1931)</item>
                <item>John Heldman (1931–1935)</item>
                <item>J. O. Christian (1935–1936)</item>
                <item>Don White (1936–1945)</item>
                <item>Blair Gullion (1945–1946)</item>
                <item>Hugh Greer (1946–1963)</item>
                <item>George Wigton (1963)</item>
                <item>Fred Shabel (1963–1967)</item>
                <item>Burr Carlson (1967–1969)</item>
                <item>Dee Rowe (1969–1977)</item>
                <item>Dom Perno (1977–1986)</item>
                <item>Jim Calhoun (1986–present)</item>
            </list>
            <p>Additional information about UConn athletics is available in the 
                <extref ns2:href="http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/asc/findaids/Athletic_Comm/MSS19990054.html">Athletic Communications Office Records</extref> or on the UConn Huskies 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.uconnhuskies.com/">website</extref>.</p>
        </bioghist>
